Complex types like object must match exactly to the fields in the entity,  for an entity to be included in the query result set.The order of the members in the metadata query array is not taken into account, and the API will apply the AND logical operator to these.While key order does not matter in metadata entries of type object, it does matter with those of type array provided.Updated about 1 month ago Working with metadataStatusUpdated about 1 month ago Working with metadataStatusQUICKSTARTQuickstart GuideGUIDESIntroductionAuthenticationTesting your API keyThrottlingData Types and Response FormatsErrorsAn invalid requestEntitiesMetadataQuerying metadataWorking with metadataThe metadata objectLimitationsSupported EntitiesStatusDeep LinkingTestingAPI WrappersScoped API KeyNo-code Integration PlatformsProof of Delivery RetrievalAPI REFERENCEOrganizationsGet delegatee detailsGet detailsAdministratorsDelete administratorUpdate administratorList administratorsCreate administratorWorkersWorker's Route Delivery ManifestSet worker's scheduleGet worker's scheduleDelete workerUpdate workerGet single workerGet workers by locationList Worker's Assigned TasksList workersCreate workerHubsList hubsUpdate HubCreate HubTeamsList Unassigned Tasks in a TeamDriver Time EstimateTeam Auto-DispatchDelete teamGet single teamList teamsUpdate teamCreate teamDestinationsDestination Address WarningsGet single destinationCreate destinationRecipientsGet single recipientFind recipientUpdate recipientCreate recipientTasksAutomatically assign list of tasksDelete taskClone taskComplete taskUpdate taskGet single task by shortIdGet single taskList tasksRecipient OverridesDependenciesCompletion RequirementsManual AssignmentAutomatic AssignmentStateBatch Job StatusTask Custom FieldsCreate tasks in batch - asyncCreate tasks in batchCreate taskContainersAdditional optionsUpdate tasksInsert tasks at index (or append)Get containerWebhooksAsynchronous Batch Job WebhookWebhook Payload ExamplesDelete webhook