$pop
The $pop command allows for the removal of one or more metadata entries for a given entity.Here is an example of a task entity before a $pop request:
JSON{
  "id": "LDJXqd2HEoGVhgmjxOawxgjF",
  // ..."metadata": [
    {
      "name": "customerId",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "4ef29b3e84eba9f2",
      "visibility": [
        "api"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "isDisenfranchised",
      "type": "boolean",
      "value": true,
      "visibility": [
        "api"
      ]
    }
  ]
}

Request
Shell$ curl -X PUT "https://onfleet.com/api/v2/tasks/LDJXqd2HEoGVhgmjxOawxgjF" \
       -u "cd3b3de84cc1ee040bf06512d233719c:" \
       -d '{"metadata":{"$pop":[{"name":"isDisenfranchised"}]}}'

JSON{
  "id": "LDJXqd2HEoGVhgmjxOawxgjF",
  // ..."metadata": [
    {
      "name": "customerId",
      "type": "string",
      "value": "4ef29b3e84eba9f2",
      "visibility": [
        "api"
      ]
    }
  ]
}

